(1, 1, '2010-07-26 07:46:41', 'francek@volnej.cz, emil@dezo.cz, jakubmatas@gmail.com, jarda@uhor.cz, jindra@jindra.cz, jjj@seynam.com', 'Předmět', '<p> </p>\r\n<h1>Vítejte u nás</h1>\r\n<p>The following example shows how form elements can be used within a <em>DataTables</em> enhanced table. The trick here is that <em>DataTables</em> does not  include the DOM elements which are not currently being displayed,  therefore you need to add a submit event handler to gather together all  of the input elements from the table, and then use the handy jQuery <strong>serialize()</strong> function to string together the data. It can then be posted to the  server as you wish.</p>', ''),
